external_knowledge:
- A 'Veteran' is a player with more than 50 games played;
- An 'Experienced' player has played more than 20 games;
- A 'Rookie' is a player with 20 or fewer games played.

- 'seasoned veterans' refers to players with more than 5 years of professional experience;
- 'wise pitching coach' refers to a coach with more than 10 years of experience and the role of 'Pitching Coach';
- 'strong lineup' refers to teams with more than 2 players;
- 'roles on the field' refers to the positions played by the players in the game;
- 'batting average greater than 0.25' is a measure of a player's hitting performance.

- 'Catchers with the golden gloves' refers to the top three catchers based on their fielding percentage;
- 'Wise mentors guiding them through the game' refers to the coaches of these catchers;
- 'Fielding percentage' is a measure of a player's defensive performance, indicating the percentage of times a player successfully handles a play.

- "High-performing players" refers to players with a batting average > 0.250, a slugging percentage > 0.400, and an on-base percentage > 0.350;
- "Long-term contracts" refers to contracts longer than 3 years;
- "Good salaries" refers to salaries greater than 3 million;
- "Winning home games" refers to games where the team won and the game was played at home.

sql:
SELECT AVG(T1.batting_average) AS average_batting_average
FROM game_stats AS T1
WHERE T1.games_played >= 50 AND T1.home_runs > (
    SELECT AVG(home_runs) 
    FROM game_stats
);

